    "abstract": "<jats:p>We study how discounting and monitoring jointly determine whether cooperation is possible in repeated games with imperfect (public or private) monitoring. Our main result provides a simple bound on the strength of players' incentives as a function of discounting, monitoring precision, and on\u2010path payoff variance. We show that the bound is tight in the low\u2010discounting/low\u2010monitoring double limit, by establishing a public\u2010monitoring folk theorem where the discount factor and the monitoring structure can vary simultaneously.</jats:p>",
